<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="marry-v">marry <strong><em>v</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'mæri/    美 /'mæri/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-vt">1.★ <strong>vt 娶；嫁；和 ... 结婚：</strong></h4>
<ul>
<li>marry sb 与某人结婚：</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>On returning to the palace, the king marries the woman.
一回到宫殿，国王就和这位女子结婚了。</p></div>

<p>注: 和某人结婚，直接表达为marry sb，不用介词。口语中更常用get married。<br />
- marry sb to sb 把某人嫁给某人；为某人娶亲：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>My father’s trying to marry me to his accountant’s daughter.
我父亲想让我娶他会计的女儿。</p></div>

<h4 id="2-vi">2.★ <strong>vi 结婚；结合：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>My uncle didn’t marry until he was forty-five. 
我叔叔直到45岁才结婚。</p></div></div>